---
// WhatItCovers.astro — Section 2: five field groups as card grid
---
<section id="what-it-covers">
  <div class="content-width">
    <h2>Everything you need to describe a brew.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      BrewSpec covers the full record — what went in, what the setup was, and what came out.
    </p>

    <div class="field-groups">
      <div class="field-group">
        <span class="field-group-tag">Brew</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Brew date (date-only or full datetime)</li>
          <li>Brew type (espresso, pour over, immersion, hybrid)</li>
          <li>Dose (g)</li>
          <li>Water weight (g) and temperature (°C)</li>
          <li>Brew method (freeform — "Hario V60", "AeroPress")</li>
          <li>Grind setting (espresso through coarse)</li>
          <li>Duration (seconds)</li>
          <li>Brew-process notes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="field-group">
        <span class="field-group-tag">Coffee</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Origin</li>
          <li>Elevation (meters above sea level)</li>
          <li>Roaster</li>
          <li>Roast level (light, medium, dark)</li>
          <li>Roast date</li>
          <li>Type (single origin, blend)</li>
          <li>Varietal</li>
          <li>Process (washed, natural, honey, etc.)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="field-group">
        <span class="field-group-tag">Water</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Dissolved solids (ppm)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="field-group">
        <span class="field-group-tag">Equipment</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Grinder model</li>
          <li>Brewer model</li>
          <li>Grinder setting (dial position)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="field-group field-group--wide">
        <span class="field-group-tag">Result</span>
        <ul>
          <li>TDS and extraction yield</li>
          <li>Brix</li>
          <li>Yield weight (g) — output weight in the cup; primary espresso metric</li>
          <li>Tasting notes (sensory description — kept separate from process notes)</li>
          <li>Ratings: overall, fragrance, aroma, flavour, acidity, aftertaste, sweetness, mouthfeel — 1–9 scale aligned to CVA hedonic protocol</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="closing-line">
      All fields optional. Record what you measure. Leave the rest blank.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .section-intro {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .field-groups {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  /* Result card spans full width */
  .field-group--wide {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .field-group {
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-md) var(--space-md) var(--space-md);
    transition: box-shadow 200ms var(--ease-out), border-color 200ms var(--ease-out);
  }

  .field-group:hover {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    border-color: var(--color-text-faint);
  }

  .field-group-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background-color: var(--color-accent-subtle);
    padding: 0.2em 0.55em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .field-group ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .field-group li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: 0.225rem 0;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  .field-group li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55em;
    width: 4px;
    height: 4px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Wide card: 2-column list on wide screens */
  .field-group--wide ul {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    column-gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .closing-line {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  @media (max-width: 639px) {
    .field-groups {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .field-group--wide {
      grid-column: auto;
    }

    .field-group--wide ul {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
